File: South Africa's Eben Etzebeth in action. JOHANNESBURG - The SA Human Rights Commission says it's disappointed the SA Rugby Union is not taking any legal action against Eben Etzebeth. READ: SAHRC wants Boks player in court over racial abuse claims This after accusations that Etzebeth racially abused someone at a Western Cape pub. The incident allegedly happened during a scuffle in August. Etzebeth has denied the claims and remains in Japan with the Springbok team.